Shield is a term used by Mecha to express _theme_ in another CMS.

A shield is a folder with a unique name, stored in `lot\shield` folder:

~~~ .txt
lot\
 └── shield\
     ├── document\
     ├── shield-1\
     ├── shield-2\
     ├── …
     └── …
~~~

A standard shield should at least contains files that structured like this:

~~~ .txt
document/
 ├── asset/
 │   ├── css/
 │   │   ├── document.css
 │   │   └── document.min.css
 │   └── js/
 │       ├── document.js
 │       └── document.min.js
 ├── state/
 │   └── config.php
 ├── 404.php
 ├── about.page
 ├── bottom.php
 ├── footer.php
 ├── header.php
 ├── index.php
 ├── menu.php
 ├── page.php
 ├── pages.php
 └── top.php
~~~

### Error

Minimum requirements for `404.php` file:

~~~ .html
<?php Shield::get('top'); ?>
<p>404 not found!</p>
<?php Shield::get('bottom'); ?>
~~~

### Index

This file contains custom functions used by the shield:

~~~ .php
<?php

Asset::set('css/document.min.css');
Asset::set('js/document.min.js');
~~~

### Top

Minimum requirements for `404.php` file:

~~~ .html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <meta charset="<?php echo $site->charset; ?>">
    <link href="<?php echo $url; ?>/favicon.ico" rel="shortcut icon">
    <title><?php echo To::text($site->page->title); ?></title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <h1><?php echo $site->title; ?></h1>
      <p><?php echo $site->slogan; ?></p>
    </header>
~~~

### Bottom

Minimum requirements for `bottom.php` file:

~~~ .html
    <footer>
      <p>&#x00A9; <?php echo $date->year; ?></p>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
~~~

### Page

Minimum requirements for `page.php` file:

~~~ .html
<main>
  <article>
    <h3><?php echo $page->title; ?></h3>
    <div><?php echo $page->content; ?></div>
  </article>
  <nav><?php echo $pager; ?></nav>
</main>
~~~

### Pages

Minimum requirements for `pages.php` file:

~~~ .html
<main>
  <?php if ($pages): ?>
  <?php foreach ($pages as $page): ?>
  <article>
    <h4><a href="<?php echo $page->url; ?>"><?php echo $page->title; ?></a></h4>
    <div><?php echo $page->content; ?></div>
  </article>
  <?php endforeach; ?>
  <?php endif; ?>
  <nav><?php echo $pager; ?></nav>
</main>
~~~

### Menu

Minimum requirements for `menu.php` file:

~~~ .html
<nav>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="<?php echo $url; ?>">Home</a></li>
    <li><a href="<?php echo $url; ?>/about">About</a></li>
    <li><a href="<?php echo $url; ?>/archive">Archive</a></li>
  </ul>
</nav>
~~~

### About

Minimum requirements for `about.page` file:

~~~ .yaml
---
title: Shield Title
description: Shield description.
author: Shield Author
link: http://example.com
version: 1.0.0
...

<p>Usage, external credits, etc.</p>
~~~